FBIS4-40011 "drsov113_f_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 National Affairs Another Water Leak Reported Another Water Leak Reported LD1106220894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 2105 GMT 11 Jun 94 LD1106220894 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] On 11 June a water leak was discovered at the Chernobyl nuclear power station in Ukraine. The water was leaking from the holding reservoir of the power generating unit No. 2. The reservoir is used to store cassettes with worked-out fuel. A shift leader at the Chernobyl nuclear power station, Aleksandr Yelchishchev, said the leak had not led to changes in background radiation levels in the nearby premises. Let me remind you that in accordance with the existing schedule, power generating unit No. 2 is currently undergoing decommissioning.
